<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Pepper'sGlasses     11-09 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Pepper's Glasses,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Glasses Stolen From Statue of Late Congressman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Someone stole the five-pound bronze wire-framed
glasses from a statue of the late Rep. Claude Pepper.
   The frames were soldered to the 9-foot statue's nose and ears.
   Sculptor Tony Lopez said he has a way to foil any similar thefts
on his likeness of the venerable Miami Democrat, who died in May.
   ``I'm going to make him contact lenses.''
   Kidding aside, Lopez said he plans to attach the next pair of
glasses _ at a cost of $100 to $300 _ with screws imbedded in the
figure.
   The theft from the statue in Jose Marti Park was discovered
Monday by Lazaro Albo, who headed the drive that raised $60,000 to
pay for the monument.
</TEXT>
