<FILEID>AP-NR-11-09-89 0458EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-RapeInitiation     11-09 0403</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Rape Initiation,0412</SECOND>
<HEAD>Female Gang Member May Have Forced 11-year-old Into Rape Initiation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 11-year-old girl who was repeatedly
raped as part of a gang's initiation may have been forced into the
ordeal by a friend, a 17-year-old female member of the gang, police
said.
   Five members of the Gangster Disciples were charged Wednesday
with raping the girl Saturday night, but Jefferson County Sheriff's
Deputy Charles Buchannon said as many as 10 or 20 young men may
have been involved.
   The young men apparently considered the rapes to be a rite of
initiation for the girl, making her their ``queen,'' said Deputy
Tony Pippen. ``Queen'' describes a girl who has been initiated by
having sex with all of a gang's members, he said.
   Gang members usually try to entice a girl, normally someone they
know, into participating willingly in the initiation, Pippen said.
In this case, he said, the girl apparently did not participate
willingly but was too afraid to resist.
   The incident started while the girl was staying at the home of
her 17-year-old friend, a gang member, police said. They said the
older girl tried to talk her friend into going outside for a walk.
   ``The girl didn't want to, but her friend dragged her out, even
though she knew what was waiting for that little girl,'' Buchannon
said. The girl was taken by her older friend and the gang members
to a park where the rapes took place, he said.
   ``The gang members let the girl go when they started worrying
about whether they'd get caught,'' Buchannon said. At least one of
the boys threatened to kill her if she told anyone, he said.
   The girl returned to her friend's house after the rape and did
not call authorities or her parents, Buchannon said.
   Residents who heard about the rape flagged down Pippen and his
partner during their patrol Sunday and told them about it. The
deputies found the girl still at her friend's house and questioned
her. The five gang members were arrested later Sunday.
   Antonio Jones, 18, was charged as an adult and the four others
were charged with being juvenile deliquents accused of rape,
Buchannon said. Three are 17 and one is 14.
   He said that to his knowledge, none of the five, all students at
Brighton High School, had been in trouble before. He described them
as being from middle-class families.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
