<HEAD>Jagger at 46: Fit and Fatherly</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At 46, the baddest boy of rock 'n' roll is also
the father of four, ages 4-19.
   ``I get on fine with my kids,'' said Mick Jagger. ``I mean, when
I tell them the dangers of drugs or sex, at least they know that I
know what I'm talking about.''
   Sometimes the father instinct reacts first, like last year when
18-year-old daughter Jade (by ex-wife Bianca) was expelled from
private school for a late-night rendezvous with her boyfriend, who
was later arrested on drug conspiracy charges.
   ``I was a little shocked for a moment,'' Jagger said in an
interview in this week's US magazine.
   ``I just let it run its course and tried to be as fair-handed as
I could be,'' he said. ``Jade had her rebellious moment, which was
pretty quiet compared to mine, which lasted about 15 years!''
   What's post-rebellion life like? ``I do a lot of boring
exercises and I lay off the goodies,'' said Jagger. ``We behave _
we have to at our age.''
   Jagger got a $3 million advance to write his autobiography, the
magazine said. But it seems an unlikely proposition.
   ``I can't remember what happened,'' the Rolling Stone's lead
singer said.
