<FIRST>r i PM-Poland-Kohl     11-09 0308</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poland-Kohl,0317</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kohl's Schedule Changed Again Hours Before Visit to Begin</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DEBORAH G. SEWARD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl arrived
today for a six-day visit that will take him to Auschwitz and the
ethnic German region of Krzyzowa.
   It marked the first visit to Poland by a West German leader
since 1977 and Kohl's first meeting with new Prime Minister Tadeusz
Mazowiecki. Kohl brought a $1 billion aid package that the first
non-Communist government in the East bloc hopes will help secure
democratic reforms.
   Mazowiecki, the former Solidarity editor elected two months ago,
and several other top Polish government officials greeted Kohl at
Warsaw's Okecie airport.
   Kohl exchanged words with school children in the welcoming party
before leaving for talks with Mazowiecki.
   Earlier today, sources disclosed that Kohl's visit to the
Auschwitz concentration camp had been changed because the head of
West Germany's Jewish community, Heinz Galinski, said he could not
join the event on the Sabbath.
   Among the 4 million victims of the Holocaust's most infamous
concentration camp were 2.5 million Jews.
   Polish and West German officials arranging the trip held an
emergency meeting today and agreed that Kohl and the others would
go to Auschwitz on Sunday.
   Emotional sensitivity still runs high in both nations which have
yet to overcome memories of old territorial disputes and the legacy
of the Nazi era.
   Polish discomfort over a visit by Kohl to Gora Sw. Anny, known
in German as Annaberg, the site of a bloody battle in 1921 over
whether the area should go to Poland or Germany forced a search for
another place for Kohl to meet with ethnic Germans.
   So instead Kohl will travel on Sunday to Krzyzowa, a Silesian
town where Nazi resisters met during the war, Jaroslaw Szczepanski,
deputy director of the government press office.
</TEXT>
