<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Magdeleine     11-09 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Magdeleine,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Author, Founder of Roman Catholic Order, Dead at 91</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Petite Soeur Magdeleine de Jesus, author and
founder of an order of Roman Catholic nuns, has died at the age of
91.
   She died Monday at the order's headquarters in Rome, where her
funeral is scheduled Friday.
   Born Magdeleine Hutin at Montigny-les-Metz in eastern France on
April 26, 1898, she founded the Fraternite des Petites Soeurs de
Jesus _ the Little Sisters of Jesus _ in 1939, in the Saharan
outpost of Touggourt, Algeria.
   The order, which has 1,400 nuns of about 60 nationalities on
five continents, is devoted to the contemplative life in the middle
of the active world. Its members share the poverty and social
condition of manual laborers in slums and shantytowns around the
world.
   She wrote two works, ``From One End of the Earth to the Other,''
and ``From the Sahara to the Whole World.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
