<TEXT>
   West German politicians praised
communist East Germany's decision Thursday to open its borders and
said the Berlin Wall had lost its purpose.
   Chancellor Helmut Kohl, on a state visit to Poland, said he
wanted to meet soon with Egon Krenz, who became the East German
