<SECOND>AM-Obit-Edhie,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sarwo Edhie, Retired General, Dies of Brain Hemorrhage</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Suharto is full name, graf 2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retired Lt. Gen. Sarwo Edhie, who led
army troops in suppressing a Communist coup attempt in 1965, died
Thursday of a brain hemorrhage at the Jakarta Military Hospital, a
military official said. He was 62.
   Edhie also helped bring the present government of President
Suharto to power.
   He had been in ill health and under medical treatment since
March, said Saukat Banjarsari, Suharto's military secretary.
   Edhie joined the army in 1943 when he was only 16 years old to
fight for the country's independence from the Netherlands.
   His last important position was as a member of Parliament, from
which he resigned in 1988.
   He is survived by his wife and seven children.
