<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
205,786 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
223,452, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 255,060 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 131,900 cars this week,
compared with 144,105 a week ago and 165,997 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 73,886,
compared with last week's 79,347 and last year's 89,063.
   Canadian automakers were to build 26,745 cars this week, up from
26,037 a week ago and from last year's 16,207.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 16,550,
compared with 17,055 a week ago and 20,150 in the same week last
year.
