   Excluding food and energy prices that are subject to large
fluctuations from month to month, however, the increase was 0.1
percent.
   Analysts said those figures provided fresh support for hopes
that inflationary pressures would remain subdued enough to keep
interest rates from rising significantly and allow for continued
economic growth.
   The Federal Reserve seemed to signal in advance its favorable
view of the inflation outlook with a move this week to relax its
credit policy slightly.
   Consolidated Freightways fell 2[ to 28\ in active trading. The
company said its results for the fourth quarter would be around the
break-even point, or possibly a loss.
